item.title: Java 6
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

semaphore:

In anticipated response to anyone that has nothing but venom towards windows, I personally think that hating everything microsoft has become the ‘trendy’ thing to do. It seems that many have a tendency to drink the same kool-aid when it comes to hating it. Linux has become the ‘trendy anti-trend’. Linux has very little appeal to me. Besides ksh/bash/csh I cannot think of anything that would possess me to give up an OS with a rich window manager for an OS that has a shoddy UI (in comparison). Doing so for the sake of ‘sticking it to the man’ is not a good enough reason for me. Suse 10.2 or 10.1 and ubuntu are decent visually but I run far too many things that are windows specific, visual studio 2005 is the first that comes to mind.

I have no problem with windows, but I would never shell out my hard earned cash for it, the price difference bewtween it and linux is not worth it at all. I play games on windows, run any windows specific programs that I must use on windows, but do all my programming and everything else on linux. The best GUI for linux in my opinion is KDE, currently I use kubuntu but I am soon installing Gentoo w/ KDE. Basically even when I go to switch to windows vista I won’t pay for it

On topic, I have had some time to read up on Java 6 since my first post, it looks great, especially the java 2d and 3d enhancements, that in my opinion is where java needed the most work.
